subSection.paragraph:
This species group was recognised by 
Huber (2011)
. It currently includes 44 species and is widely distributed in central and southern China, as well as Thailand (
Huber 2011
; 
Zhu et al. 2018
; 
Lan et al. 2020
). Six new species are described below.

